sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
A node is a machine which is part of the Jenkins environment and capable of executing Jobs. This actions creates a node which can be launched using Java Web Start software.

Inputs:

  • Node Name - Name of the node to be created. E.g . Test_node.
  • Node Description - Description of the node to be created.
  • Number Of Executors - The maximum number of concurrent builds that Jenkins may perform on this agent.
  • Remote Root Directory - Remote directory to be associated with this node. E.g. 'C:\Jenkins'.
  • Label - Label to be associated with this node. E.g. 'Test'.
  • Usage - Controls how Jenkins schedules builds on this node. List of possible options:
    • Normal - Sets the node to 'Use this node as much as possible' mode. In this mode, Jenkins uses this node freely. Whenever there is a build that can be done by using this node, Jenkins will use it.
    • Exclusive - Sets the node to 'Only build jobs with label expressions matching this node' mode.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".

Error Messages:

  • A node already exists with the given name.
  • Provided value for Number of Executors must be greater than or equal to 1.
  • The request could not be fulfilled due to invalid characters in node name.
  • Provided value one of the inputs is invalid.
  • Invalid username or password/token.
  • The Jenkins server is being restarted.
  • You do not have enough permissions to perform this action in Jenkins server.

Additional Note:

  • Java Web Start makes use of Java Network Launch Protocol(JNLP) to establish a connection from the Master node to the Slave node. For more details, click here.

To use this action, the corresponding Jenkins connection and credential must be created and associated with the Jenkins Connection & Credential alias.

Disclaimer:Jenkins and Jenkins logo are a registered trademark of Jenkins.

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
